<paragraph id="016C1165FFFB3923EBD2C212FD615DDA" blockId="85.[225,1437,1269,1773]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">
At least nine sciaenid species are represented in our material, 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFFB3923E8DCC212FA675E0D" authority="(Koken, 1888)" baseAuthorityName="Koken" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[1005,1432,1313,1339]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Ekokenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="eporrecta">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFFB3923E8DCC212FB275E0D" box="[1005,1240,1313,1339]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Ekokenia eporrecta</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="65426C94FFFB3923EFDCC212FA715E0D" author="Koken" box="[1261,1422,1313,1339]" firstAuthor="Koken" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" pagination="274 - 305" refId="ref54599" refString="Koken E. 1888. Neue Untersuchungen an tertiaren Fisch-Otolithen. Zeitschrift der deutschen geologischen Gesellschaft 40: 274 - 305." type="journal article" year="1888">Koken, 1888</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFFB3923EBD2C270FD0D5E6B" authority="Stringer et al., 2022" authorityName="Stringer" authorityYear="2022" box="[227,754,1346,1373]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Eosciaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ebersolei">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFFB3923EBD2C270FE265E6A" box="[227,473,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Eosciaena ebersolei</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="65426C94FFFB3923EAD8C271FD0D5E6B" author="Stringer" box="[489,754,1346,1373]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Stringer" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" pagination="1" refId="ref58202" refString="Stringer G. L., Parmley D. &amp; Quinn A. 2022. Eocene teleostean otoliths, including a new taxon, from the Clinchfield Formation (Bartonian) in Georgia, USA, with biostratigraphic, biogeographic, and paleoecologic implications. Palaeovertebrata 45 (1): e 1. https: // doi. org / 10.18563 / pv. 45.1. e 1" type="journal article" year="2022">
Stringer 
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFFB3923E969C270FD635E6A" box="[600,668,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">et al.</emphasis>
, 2022
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFFB3923E837C271FAD55E6B" authority="Dante &amp; Frizzell, 1965" authorityName="Dante &amp; Frizzell" authorityYear="1965" box="[774,1322,1346,1373]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Jefitchia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="copelandi">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFFB3923E837C271FC115E6A" box="[774,1006,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Jefitchia copelandi</emphasis>
Dante &amp; 
<bibRefCitation id="65426C94FFFB3923EF4DC271FAD55E6B" author="Frizzell D. L." box="[1148,1322,1346,1373]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" pagination="85 - 110" refId="ref53928" refString="Frizzell D. L. 1965. Otolith-based genera and lineages of fossil bonefishes (Clupeiformes, Albulidae). Senckenbergiana Lethaea 46 a: 85 - 110." type="book chapter" year="1965">Frizzell, 1965</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFFB3923EE0EC270FD405E49" authority="(Dante &amp; Frizzell, 1965)" baseAuthorityName="Dante &amp; Frizzell" baseAuthorityYear="1965" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Sciaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pseudoradians">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFFB3923EE0EC270FE6F5E48" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Sciaena pseudoradians</emphasis>
(Dante &amp; 
<bibRefCitation id="65426C94FFFB3923E93EC257FD495E49" author="Frizzell D. L." box="[527,694,1380,1407]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" pagination="85 - 110" refId="ref53928" refString="Frizzell D. L. 1965. Otolith-based genera and lineages of fossil bonefishes (Clupeiformes, Albulidae). Senckenbergiana Lethaea 46 a: 85 - 110." type="book chapter" year="1965">Frizzell, 1965</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, “ 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFFB3923E9E8C257FCC95E48" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[729,822,1380,1406]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Sciaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFFB3923E9E8C257FCC95E48" box="[729,822,1380,1406]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Sciaena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFFB3923E87AC257FB5A5E48" authority="(Koken, 1888)" baseAuthorityName="Koken" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[843,1189,1380,1406]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Jefitchia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="claybornensis">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFFB3923E87AC257FC115E48" box="[843,1006,1380,1406]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">claybornensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="65426C94FFFB3923E8CFC257FB645E48" author="Koken" box="[1022,1179,1380,1406]" firstAuthor="Koken" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" pagination="274 - 305" refId="ref54599" refString="Koken E. 1888. Neue Untersuchungen an tertiaren Fisch-Otolithen. Zeitschrift der deutschen geologischen Gesellschaft 40: 274 - 305." type="journal article" year="1888">Koken, 1888</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, “ 
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFFB3923EF8FC257FB2B5E48" box="[1214,1236,1380,1406]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">S.</emphasis>
” 
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFFB3923EFD8C256FACB5E48" box="[1257,1332,1381,1406]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">eanesi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="65426C94FFFB3923EE75C257FEDE5EA9" author="Muller" firstAuthor="Muller" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" pagination="1 - 360" refId="ref55491" refString="Muller A. 1999. Ichthyofaunen aus dem atlantischen Tertiar der USA. Leipziger Geowissenschaften 9 / 10: 1 - 360." type="journal article" year="1999">Müller, 1999</bibRefCitation>
), “ 
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFFB3923EA77C2B5FEA35E96" box="[326,348,1414,1440]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">S.</emphasis>
” 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFFB3923EA42C2B6FD525EA9" authority="(Koken, 1888)" baseAuthorityName="Koken" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[371,685,1413,1439]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Sciaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFFB3923EA42C2B6FE0D5EA9" box="[371,498,1413,1439]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">intermedia</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="65426C94FFFB3923E935C2B6FD5B5EA9" author="Koken" box="[516,676,1413,1439]" firstAuthor="Koken" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" pagination="274 - 305" refId="ref54599" refString="Koken E. 1888. Neue Untersuchungen an tertiaren Fisch-Otolithen. Zeitschrift der deutschen geologischen Gesellschaft 40: 274 - 305." type="journal article" year="1888">Koken, 1888</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, “ 
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFFB3923E9F8C2B5FD205E96" box="[713,735,1414,1440]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">S.</emphasis>
” 
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFFB3923E9C7C2B6FCAF5EA9" box="[758,848,1413,1439]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">livesayi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="65426C94FFFB3923E853C2B6FBFD5EA9" author="Muller" box="[866,1026,1413,1439]" firstAuthor="Muller" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" pagination="1 - 360" refId="ref55491" refString="Muller A. 1999. Ichthyofaunen aus dem atlantischen Tertiar der USA. Leipziger Geowissenschaften 9 / 10: 1 - 360." type="journal article" year="1999">Müller, 1999</bibRefCitation>
), and one undescribed species (as 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFFB3923EBD2C295FE9D5EF6" authorityName="Cuvier" authorityYear="1829" box="[227,354,1446,1472]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Sciaenidae</taxonomicName>
indet.). The relationships of these sciaenids are still obscure and a point of discussion (
<bibRefCitation id="65426C94FFFB3923EBDAC2FBFE335ED4" author="Schwarzhans" box="[235,460,1480,1506]" firstAuthor="Schwarzhans" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" pagination="1 - 245" refId="ref56714" refString="Schwarzhans W. 1993. A comparative morphological treatise of recent and fossil otoliths of the family Sciaenidae (Perciformes). In: Pfeil F. (ed.) Piscium Catalogus, Otolithi Piscium: 1 - 245. Verlag Dr. Freidrich Pfeil, Munich." type="book chapter" year="1993">Schwarzhans 1993</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="65426C94FFFB3923EAE9C2FBFDAC5ED4" author="Nolf" box="[472,595,1480,1506]" firstAuthor="Nolf" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" refId="ref55849" refString="Nolf D. 2013. The Diversity of Fish Otoliths, Past and Present. Royal Belgian Institute of Natural Sciences, Brussels." type="book" year="2013">Nolf 2013</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="65426C94FFFB3923E96EC2FBFCB15ED4" author="Ebersole" box="[607,846,1480,1506]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Ebersole" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" refId="ref53603" refString="Ebersole J. A., Cicimurri D. J. &amp; Stringer G. L. 2019. Taxonomy and biostratigraphy of the elasmobranchs and bony fishes (Chondrichthyes and Osteichthyes) of the lower - to - middle Eocene (Ypresian to Bartonian) Claiborne Group in Alabama, USA, including an analysis of otoliths. European Journal of" type="book" year="2019">
Ebersole 
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFFB3923E9FCC2FAFCFF5ED4" box="[717,768,1480,1506]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">et al</emphasis>
. 2019
</bibRefCitation>
), which is mainly due to plesiomorphic conditions concerning the modern analogs. Using landmark analysis, the geometric morphometrics of these otoliths quantitatively showed at least two clear divisions (Lin, unpublished conference data,Supplementary file 1, not including the recently described 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFFB3923E9ABC11EFC775D70" box="[666,904,1580,1606]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Eosciaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ebersolei">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFFB3923E9ABC11EFC775D70" box="[666,904,1580,1606]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Eosciaena ebersolei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
): one with shorter cauda and wider distance between the ostium and the bent part of the cauda, including 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFFB3923E8E4C17DFB955D51" baseAuthorityName="Koken" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[981,1130,1614,1639]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Ekokenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="eporrecta">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFFB3923E8E4C17DFB955D51" box="[981,1130,1614,1639]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">E. eporrecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, “ 
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFFB3923EFB8C17DFB605D5E" box="[1161,1183,1614,1640]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">S.</emphasis>
” 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFFB3923EF86C17EFAA55D51" baseAuthorityName="Koken" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[1207,1370,1613,1639]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Jefitchia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="claybornensis">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFFB3923EF86C17EFAA55D51" box="[1207,1370,1613,1639]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">claybornensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, “ 
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFFB3923EE48C17DFA705D5E" box="[1401,1423,1614,1640]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">S.</emphasis>
” 
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFFB3923EBD2C15CFED15DBE" box="[227,302,1647,1672]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">eanesi</emphasis>
, and the undescribed species. The other cluster of otoliths, with a relatively long cauda and wide ostium, includes 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFFB3923EAC8C1A2FD725D9C" authorityName="Dante &amp; Frizzell" authorityYear="1965" box="[505,653,1680,1706]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Jefitchia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="copelandi">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFFB3923EAC8C1A2FD725D9C" box="[505,653,1680,1706]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">J. copelandi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFFB3923E991C1A3FC905D9C" baseAuthorityName="Dante &amp; Frizzell" baseAuthorityYear="1965" box="[672,879,1680,1706]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Sciaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pseudoradians">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFFB3923E991C1A3FC905D9C" box="[672,879,1680,1706]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">S. pseudoradians</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, “ 
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFFB3923E8BEC1A3FC5A5D9C" box="[911,933,1680,1706]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">S.</emphasis>
” 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFFB3923E88FC1A3FBC25D9C" baseAuthorityName="Koken" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[958,1085,1680,1706]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Sciaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFFB3923E88FC1A3FBC25D9C" box="[958,1085,1680,1706]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">intermedia</emphasis>
